<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Zulu_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Vowels">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Vowels">Vowels</span></h3>
<table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="4" class="wikitable">
<tr>
<th>IPA</th>
<th>Example (IPA)</th>
<th>Example (Written)</th>
<th>Meaning</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[i]</span></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[síːza̤]</span></td>
<td><i>-siza</i></td>
<td>"help"</td>
<td>This vowel is pronounced somewhat like <i>ease</i> in <a href="/wiki/English_language" title="English language">English</a>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[u]</span></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[umúːzi̤]</span></td>
<td><i>umuzi</i></td>
<td>"homestead"</td>
<td>Somewhat like English vowel in the word <i>loom</i>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[e]</span></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[umɡiɓéːli]</span></td>
<td><i>umgibeli</i></td>
<td>"passenger"</td>
<td>e is <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">e</span> when the following syllable contains an "i" or a "u", or final</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[ɛ]</span></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[pʰɛ́ːɠa]</span></td>
<td><i>-pheka</i></td>
<td>"cook"</td>
<td>e is <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">ɛ</span> everywhere else</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[o]</span></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[umaɠóːti]</span></td>
<td><i>umakoti</i></td>
<td>"bride"</td>
<td>o is <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">o</span> when the following syllable contains an "i" or a "u", or final</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[ɔ]</span></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[ɔɡɔ̤̌ːɡo̤]</span></td>
<td><i>ogogo</i></td>
<td>"grandmothers"</td>
<td>o is <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">ɔ</span> everywhere else</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[a]</span></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[dǐ̤ːda̤]</span></td>
<td><i>-dida</i></td>
<td>"puzzle"</td>
<td>Is pronounced somewhat like <i>mama</i> in English.</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Vowels are lengthened in the penultimate syllable.</p>
